{"_id":"ViGU8ijGT4Y1WOWq","name":"Armor of the Sunken King","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, very rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>The scent of brine and fresh seaweed accompanies this breastplate, no matter how hard you scrub. When donning this armor, you hear the faint rumble of distant thundering waves as it passes over your head.</p>\n<p>You have a +2 bonus to AC while you wear this armor and gain the following effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You speak abyssal fluently.</li>\n<li>You can breathe water.</li>\n<li>You can&rsquo;t float in water and instead sink at a rate of 60 feet per round. Walking on the bed of a water body is not difficult terrain for you.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>Sunken King's Favour.</em></strong> As an action you can cast <a> Arcane Hand</a> without any components. When cast in this way, the spell is modified as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The hand takes the form of two Medium spectral tentacles, sprouting from the shoulders of the Breastplate. They occupy your space and move with you.</li>\n<li>The reach of 'Clenched Fist', 'Forceful Hand' and 'Grasping Hand' is increased to 15 feet.</li>\n<li>'Interposing Hand&rsquo; can only be used on yourself.</li>\n<li>You can maintain two of the spell's effects simultaneously (e.g. use Clenched Fist or Forceful Hand when you still have a target grappled with Grasping Hand), but can only command one of the tentacles with your bonus action each turn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The attack roll modifier for &lsquo;Clenched Fist&rsquo; equals <strong>4</strong> plus your <strong>proficiency bonus</strong>. Once you use this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until the armor spends 8 hours submerged in saltwater.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.SK2HATQ4abKUlV8i]{Breastplate} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.6MuBIUNkdVQxhgQ1]{Breastplate of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.rLMflzmxpe8JGTOA]{Chain Mail} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.ZC2cle6wkgTEvabb]{Chain Mail of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.p2zChy24ZJdVqMSH]{Chain Shirt} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.ZC2cle6wkgTEvabb]{Chain Mail of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.vsgmACFYINloIdPm]{Half Plate Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.IXQHVhjUsS4vR6Nn]{Half Plate Armor of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.n1V07puo0RQxPGuF]{Hide Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.0bMvm32SjeeULgu4]{Hide Armor of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.OjkIqlW2UpgFcjZa]{Plate Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.5TU8nQ0JxviQ1jTt]{Plate Armor of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.nsXZejlmgalj4he9]{Ring Mail} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.3luiD1783YZqOBl8]{Ring Mail of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.XmnlF5fgIO3tg6TG]{Scale Mail} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.xP7MBbsUBFquFv9N]{Scale Mail of the Sunken King})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.cKpJmsJmU8YaiuqG]{Splint Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.MtaFhHRzEi4NJ3JY]{Splint Armor of the Sunken King})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Very Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":2,"type":"bonus","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"magicitems":{"enabled":false,"charges":"0","chargeType":"c1","destroy":false,"rechargeable":false,"recharge":"0","rechargeType":"t1","rechargeUnit":"r1"},"betterRolls5e":{"critRange":{"value":null},"critDamage":{"value":""},"quickDesc":{"value":true,"altValue":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true,"altValue":true},"quickOther":{"value":true,"altValue":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true,"altValue":true},"quickCharges":{"value":{"quantity":false},"altValue":{"quantity":false}}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.Pfyx1zPPkUej0EDI"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Breastplate_of_the_Sunken_King.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sir Wrenchy the Third","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Simple weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Ajyq6nGwF7FtLhDQ]{Mace}), melee weapon, very rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n<br />4 lb.\n<br />[[/r 1d6]] bludgeoning\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p><em>Sir Wrenchy the Third</em> is an eccentric wrench, given sentience after years of being used to create items imbued with magic. You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. While holding this weapon, you have advantage on Intelligence checks and saving throws. Spells cast from the wrench have a save DC of 15. The wrench consists of two parts, and pulling them apart reveals a dagger sheathed in the wrench's handle. If you are not attuned to the wrench when you unsheathe the dagger you take [[/r 1d4]] bludgeoning damage as Sir Wrenchinald Clamps down on your hand.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Foul Mouth.</em></strong> You can use bonus action to prompt sir Wrenchy to hurl insults at a nearby creature in order to cast @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.cdrYKaFi98YWaBMw]{Vicious Mockery}on the target.</p> <p><strong><em>Pun Master.</em></strong> Once per short rest, as an action you can hold out sir Wrenchy to face a creature, causing it to spurt out a series of puns, casting @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.BQk5Row4NymMnUQl]{Hideous Laughter}or compelled duel (your choice).</p> <p><strong><em>Personality.</em></strong> While sir wrenchy is being wielded it has a tendency of emitting a constant stream of peculiar observations and insults, directed at anyone who would listen. Sir wrenchy values intelligence and mechanical skill above all, and may occasionally challenge its wielder with contests of wit in order to test them. Conflict arises if it feels that its wielder does not match its intelligence or makes decisions it views as foolish. Although sir wrenchy acts as if all challenges are beneath it, it is easily intrigued by a puzzle or strange problem.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":4,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Very Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":1,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6+1+@mod","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"simpleM","properties":{"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false,"ver":false},"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.kwon6VUAe6oQgteA"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Sir_Wrenchy_the_Third.webp","effects":[],"_id":"WYbnHPTv7PGWh9Uq"}
{"_id":"Wyz7QgBwmhwnLdmp","name":"Undertaker's Cloak (Legendary)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, legendary</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Mort I. Fi&eacute;d had learned one thing whilst under his father&rsquo;s tutelage; in this world, corpses don&rsquo;t always stay corpses. When the dead start rising, you want someone to have your back. Someone&hellip; or something.</p>\n<p>Trailing from your back, ragged scraps of cloth and bandage seem to float in an ethereal wind, even on the calmest of days. As an action, you can speak the cloak&rsquo;s command word causing shreds of it to pull away and begin entangling a Large or smaller creature you can see within 10 feet of you. The target must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained }. Whilst restrained in this way a target is vulnerable to fire damage and must succeed on a DC 19 Constitution saving throw at the start of each of its turn or take [[/r 4d6]] necrotic damage as it slowly becomes mummified.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action, you can speak a second command word, releasing the target and causing the scraps of cloth to fall lifelessly to the ground. A target restrained by the cape can use an action to make a DC 19 Strength check, freeing itself on a success.</p>\n<p>Once this feature is used, it can&rsquo;t be used again until the following midnight, by which point the cloak has regrown.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"units":"","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.hMyiurjkpLpI0i2s"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Undertakers_Cloak.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Wings of Prey (Rare)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attuneme</em><em>nt)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Bestowed upon defenders of city walls and mountain rangers alike, these wings bestow great mobility, as well as packing a secret weapon. The appearance of the wings varies from individual to another, shifting in colour to mirror their soul.</p>\n<p>This item has 6 charges and recharges fully at dawn. While attuned to the wings, you have a flying speed equal to 5 multiplied by the number of remaining charges in feet. As a bonus action, you can speak the command word to make the wings appear or disappear.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Razor Sharp.</em></strong> As an action while the wings are present, you can expend 1 charge to hurl a flurry of razor-sharp feathers in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 6d6]] slashing damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":6,"max":6,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d6","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":15,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.72f4Qv8vjo6Ko090"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Wings_of_Prey_Dark.webp","effects":[],"_id":"Xz9bbq4Bxg9epOp4"}
{"_id":"Z3SNaj4Z9todvChK","name":"Shadowstalker Garb","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>This mechanical garb was tailor made for undercover assassins. Modelled after birds of preys by Anton Spark, the famous tinkerer, it allows to glide over the targets without being heard and eliminate it a swift swooping attack.</p>\n<p>Whilst attuned to this item you are proficient with the Dexterity (Acrobatics) skill. You can use your mechanical wings to slow your fall or allow you to glide. When you fall and aren't incapacitated, you can subtract up to 100 feet from the fall when calculating falling damage, and you can move up to 2 feet horizontally for every 1 foot you descend. Whilst gliding you have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth)checks to avoid being heard.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Take-off.</em></strong> You can activate your wings and gain a flying speed of 30 feet for 10 minutes. After this duration the suit will need to recharge over a short rest.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Death from Above.</em></strong> As a bonus action you may fold yourself into a dive position granting you a &lsquo;descending speed&rsquo; of 120 ft. This movement can only be used to drop directly downwards. If you hit a creature with a melee weapon attack after dropping in such a way you deal an additional [[/r 1d6]] damage for each 10 feet descended. If you miss on the attack you may use your reaction to flare your wings and pull out of the dive. Make a Dexterity (Acrobatics)check. The DC for this check starts at 0 and increases by 2 for each 10 ft. descended before the attack. On a success you swoop back up to half your previous altitude. On a failure you crash, taking [[/r 1d6]] damage per 20 ft. descended.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.SK2HATQ4abKUlV8i]{Breastplate} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.JWVRTKQNexW27LQ3]{Shadowstalker Breastplate})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.p2zChy24ZJdVqMSH]{Chain Shirt} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.RUfNV0lQ84cdxInm]{Shadowstalker Chain Shirt})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.vsgmACFYINloIdPm]{Half Plate Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.chOsqWXDmu5p5vAq]{Shadowstalker Half Plate Armor})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.n1V07puo0RQxPGuF]{Hide Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.PWPYsFHc7YcBWqrC]{Shadowstalker Hide Armor})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.WwdpHLXGX5r8uZu5]{Leather Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.oWyvAFTLWlZY9kDh]{Shadowstalker Leather Armor})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.GtKV1b5uqFQqpEni]{Padded Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.WBdqgqdGPLf44wI3]{Shadowstalker Padded Armor})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.XmnlF5fgIO3tg6TG]{Scale Mail} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.Pvq2zDRybvUk5tYC]{Shadowstalker Scale Mail})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.TIV3B1vbrVHIhQAm]{Studded Leather Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.XVPIC0SgNc2alI6P]{Shadowstalker Studded Leather Armor})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.IOZNVJEBvzfVpQcE"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Shadowstalker_Garb.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ZAazRwLw6BN5ATSC","name":"Magehunter Bulwark (Legendary)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Armor (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.sSs3hSzkKBMNBgTs]{Shield}), legendary (requires attunement)</em>\n\n<br />6 lb.\nAC +2\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Like a leaden wall, spellbreakers would encircle evil magic users, sending spells ricocheting up into the night sky. Eventually, when the enemy's magic was spent, these red and black shields would thrust forwards, hammering their foe to the ground where they could be shackled. Though few are now found, these mage hunter bulwarks are a thorn in the side of even the mightiest Lich.</p>\n<p>While wielding and attuned to this magical shield, you gain a +2 bonus to your AC and gain the &lsquo;Deflect Spell&rsquo; feature.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Deflect Spell.</em></strong> When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken, you can use your reaction to deflect some of the spell&rsquo;s energy. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack/effect is reduced by [[/r 5d10]].</p>\n\n<p>If you reduce the damage to 0, the spell has no effect on you, and you can attempt to reflect the spell&rsquo;s raw energy at its origin. Use the same spell slot level, spell save DC, attack bonus, and/or spellcasting ability of the caster/origin of the spell. On a hit or failed Dexterity saving throw, the target takes force damage equal to the damage absorbed.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, roll a [[/r d6]]. On a 1, the shield becomes overloaded and can&rsquo;t deflect spells again until you finish a long rest.</p>\n\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":"When you are hit by a spell attack, or subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to reduce or avoid the damage taken"},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":"self"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10",""]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":4,"type":"shield","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.q3GAQys8JFvsj0yM"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Bulwark.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aIC0XBpVzxWOeq3a","name":"Undertaker's Cloak (Very Rare)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Wondrous item, very rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Mort I. Fi&eacute;d had learned one thing whilst under his father&rsquo;s tutelage; in this world, corpses don&rsquo;t always stay corpses. When the dead start rising, you want someone to have your back. Someone&hellip; or something.</p>\n<p>Trailing from your back, ragged scraps of cloth and bandage seem to float in an ethereal wind, even on the calmest of days. As an action, you can speak the cloak&rsquo;s command word causing shreds of it to pull away and begin entangling a Large or smaller creature you can see within 10 feet of you. The target must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or become @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained }. Whilst restrained in this way a target is vulnerable to fire damage and must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw at the start of each of its turn or take [[/r 3d6]] necrotic damage as it slowly becomes mummified.</p>\n<p>As a bonus action, you can speak a second command word, releasing the target and causing the scraps of cloth to fall lifelessly to the ground. A target restrained by the cape can use an action to make a DC 17 Strength check, freeing itself on a success.</p>\n<p>Once this feature is used, it can&rsquo;t be used again until the following midnight, by which point the cloak has regrown.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Very Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":1,"units":"","type":"enemy"},"range":{"value":10,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":1,"max":1,"per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.zmwJ0uApE7f127GR"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Undertakers_Cloak.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Venus Fools Trap","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This cloak is made from a shapeshifting sub species of carnivorous plants. Unnatural magic is involved in the alterations necessary to transform a living creature into a garment. Yet the metamorphosis is far from perfect, and this cloak hungers for flesh. When worn, you can feel the cloak pulsing and moving around your body.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Lunch break.</em></strong> As an action, you can put the cloak on a flat non magical surface. It adapts to the surface and matches its properties. The cloak covers a surface 10 feet long and 5 feet wide. If a creature uses its action to examine the area the cloak is in, the creature can spot the hidden carnivorous item with a successful DC 17 Wisdom (Perception) check. If a creature enters the space occupied by the cloak, it must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 2d10+8]] piercing damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p> <p><strong><em>Take-out.</em></strong> When a creature enters a space within 10 feet of you, you can use your reaction to have the cloak pounce and wrap around the creature. The creature must succeed a DC15 Strength saving throw or be @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.b4UvTt9P3As79cwm]{Grappled}by the carnivorous cloak. While grappled in this way, the creature is @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.QRKWz3p6v9Rl1Tzh]{Restrained }and takes [[/r 2d8+4]] acid damage at the end of each of its turns. A creature restrained by the cloak can use its action to make a DC15 Strength check, freeing itself on a success. When a creature frees itself, the cloak falls to the ground and moves 10 feet closer to you at the start of each of your turns, until it reaches you. This property can't be used again until you finish a short or long rest.</p> <p><strong><em>Take-out.</em></strong> This cloak is cursed, a fact that is revealed only when you attune to it. Attuning to it curses you until you are targeted by the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.XZhdgVK3cLoxNCQl]{Remove Curse}spell or similar magic; removing the cloak fails to end the curse and it always seems to find its way back to you at the end of a long rest. While cursed, the cloak must feast on the corpse of at least a small creature every 24 hours. Failing to do so, causes it to slowly digest you during a long rest. When you finish a long rest, you recover one less hit dice, and take [[/r 2d6]] acid damage upon waking up.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":10,"units":"ft","type":"line"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d10+8","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":13,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.yGnwS3ixTUFkiyUW"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Venus_fools_Trap.webp","effects":[],"_id":"f824kagy5mCARuPU"}
{"_id":"i7CQRdLxS08XrBz1","name":"Magehunter Blade (Rare)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Made of a weave-intersecting alloy, these armaments were the go-to weapon for the mage-hunting Order of the Spellbreakers. Fanatical elements within the order have recently taken power, bringing with them an abhorrence for all things magical. Having largely destroyed this magical cache, such weapons are now very rare and are only wielded by the few who cling to the old ways.</p>\n<p>You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you hit a target that is under the effect of a spell or magical effect, the spell is dispelled if it is 3th-level or lower, and the target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] force damage for each level of the dispelled spell (dispelled cantrips deal no additional damage). Once a spell is dispelled, roll a [[/r d4]]. If the number is equal to or lower than the level of the dispelled spell, the blade loses this feature until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.xMkP8BmFzElcsMaR]{Greatsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.6kvDwmC08BMvhcxL]{Magehunter Greatsword (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.2iKfXBDBXQXxwStg]{Magehunter Longsword (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.B3Vq01OFjG5Tq3tf]{Magehunter Rapier (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.armFzWw3dCT9Vobn]{Magehunter Scimitar (Rare)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.osLzOwQdPtrK3rQH]{Shortsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.1lWP3QvzhNFdBLj7]{Magehunter Shortsword (Rare)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.JfYzhtRnksFGLI1b"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Blade.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Cursed Beast Serum","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"consumable","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Potion, rar</em><em>e</em>\n\n<br />8 oz.\n<hr />\n\n<p>Doctor Jake Kill advertises his proprietary blend of bull&rsquo;s pituitary and caffeine as a &ldquo;sure fire way to lose friends and alienate people. Especially if those people are a swarm of marauding goblins&rdquo;. Oddly enough he seems more than a little keen to get rid of this particular concoction...</p>\n<p>Tied up in a protective claw is a philter of bubbling red liquid. Upon consuming this potion, you are filled with a sense of rage and selfishness as your muscles inflate, and your veins bulge. For the next 10 minutes, you turn into a brute, the physical and mental manifestation of your most evil and selfish thoughts.</p>\n<p>You undergo the following changes for the duration of the potion&rsquo;s effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your size increases by one category and your weight increases by a factor of 8.</li>\n<li>You have advantage on Strength checks and saving throws.</li>\n<li>Your Strength score increases to 22, if not already higher.</li>\n<li>Your alignment changes to evil; you think of your own survival first and any trace of compassion or mercy is shredded.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After 10 minutes elapses you return to normal and gain a level of exhaustion.</p>\n<p><em><strong>GM Tip:</strong> Tell your player about the change in alignment as a whisper, and explain it makes them feel selfish and angry so they can roleplay accordingly.</em></p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0.5,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":"","autoDestroy":true,"autoUse":true},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"consumableType":"potion"},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.nK5xW90VMLOiiZ9u"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Cursed_Beast_Serum.webp","effects":[],"_id":"nJGmDfQs3YNx7Wz5"}
{"_id":"pWvu1obbB1ku6o3S","name":"Dragon Turtleâ€™s Claw","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Carved from a claw of a dragon turtle, a giant sea turtle, this huge club sports a thriving ecosystem of halophilic moss, barnacles, and seaweed. You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Turtle Steam.</em></strong> As an action you can slam the tooth into the ground, or thrust it into a body of water, creating a 30-foot-cone shockwave. All creatures in the area must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes [[/r 3d10]] fire damage and is knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. On a success, it takes half as much damage and is not knocked prone. Being underwater doesn&rsquo;t grant resistance against this damage. Once you have used this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.nfIRTECQIG81CvM4]{Club} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.6Ok7A4NIiF63JcBe]{Dragon Turtle&rsquo;s Claw (Club)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.QRCsxkCwWNwswL9o]{Greatclub} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.nHEEmM5INMRuG34q]{Dragon Turtle&rsquo;s Claw (Greatclub)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.g1T4z69p2l5UHIdu"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Leviathans_Tooth.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Wings of Prey (Very Rare)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, very rare (requires attunemen</em><em>t)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>Bestowed upon defenders of city walls and mountain rangers alike, these wings bestow great mobility, as well as packing a secret weapon. The appearance of the wings varies from individual to another, shifting in colour to mirror their soul.</p>\n<p>This item has 6 charges and recharges fully at dawn. While attuned to the wings, you have a flying speed equal to 10 multiplied by the number of remaining charges in feet. As a bonus action, you can speak the command word to make the wings appear or disappear.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Razor Sharp.</em></strong> As an action while the wings are present, you can expend 1 charge to hurl a flurry of razor-sharp feathers in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in the area must make a DC 17 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 8d6]] slashing damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Very Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":30,"units":"ft","type":"cone"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":6,"max":6,"per":"day"},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["8d6","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":17,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.Tu8oWbQiOd4LGgtr"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Wings_of_Prey_Dark.webp","effects":[],"_id":"sJymQlcNBHYnxMAz"}
{"_id":"t3XSlK7DBUYeuIA1","name":"Leviathan's Tooth","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, very rare</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Carved from the tooth of a leviathan, a giant sea snake, this huge club sports a thriving ecosystem of halophilic moss, barnacles, and seaweed. You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Leviathan's Might.</em></strong> As an action you can slam the tooth into the ground, or thrust it into a body of water, creating a 30-foot-cone shockwave. All creatures in the area must make a DC 17 Strength saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes [[/r 4d10]] thunder damage and is knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. On a success, it takes half as much damage and is not knocked prone. Once you have used this feature, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.nfIRTECQIG81CvM4]{Club} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.8muNWeLeh4B49aUj]{Leviathan's Tooth (Club)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.QRCsxkCwWNwswL9o]{Greatclub} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.WvL65pbK632ioTQ8]{Leviathan's Tooth (Greatclub)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Very Rare","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.eplvE8ipVJLIZ9D7"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Leviathans_Tooth.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Mechanical Tail (Legendary)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This item is another creation of the eccentric Anton Spark, tinkerer extraordinaire. This mechanical tail is powered by a magic-infused steam core. Any bipedal creature can wear it on its back and, once attuned, use it as if it was born with a tail.</p>\n<p>While attuned to the mechanical tail you can use it to grapple a target within reach. You have +6 bonus to Strength (Athletics) checks you make to grapple a target with this tail.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Steam-powered Strike.</em></strong> As an action, you sweep your tail with wicked, steam-powered ferocity. Each creature within 5 feet of your must succeed on a DC 19 Dexterity saving throw or take [[/r 5d10]] slashing damage and be knocked @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ZkXz0qdkNBkKE6tN]{Prone}. Roll a [[/r d4]]; on a 1 the tail runs out of steam and can't be used again until you finish a short rest</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Legendary","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":5,"units":"ft","type":"radius"},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":19,"scaling":"flat"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"clothing","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.ZvaNIMTzoypYhb5m"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Mechanical_Tail.webp","effects":[],"_id":"u1MoqvvdOzUCQc9B"}
{"_id":"uLYRPjMQWW7jzBjK","name":"Ceremonial Macuahuitl","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Martial weapon (@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword}), melee weapon, rare (requires attunement by a creature with a Strength score of 16 or more)</em>\n\n<br />6 lb.\n<br />[[/r 1d8]] slashing - versatile ([[/r 1d10]])\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This Macuahuitl, unlike traditional ones, isn&rsquo;t made of bone and wood, but gold and jade, making it exceptionally heavy. Often used during sacrificial rituals to appease the sun god, this item retains magical powers bestowed by years of ceremonial use. You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n <p><strong><em>Eclipse!</em></strong> While you hold the drawn sword in the sunlight, you can use an action to cast the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.S7VbUetIfVT7B6Eq]{Darkness}spell. This property can't be used again until you finish a short or long rest.</p> <p><strong><em>Might of the Sun God.</em></strong> While under the night sky or when you are standing in non-magical darkness, you can use an action to call upon the help of the sun god, becoming blessed with its might for the next minute. While blessed in this way, you can shoot a beam of brilliant light from the tip of the macuahuitl in a 5-foot-wide, 60-foot-long line as an action on each of your turns. Each creature in the line must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes [[/r 6d8]] radiant damage and is blinded until the end of your next turn. On a successful save, it takes half as much damage and isn&rsquo;t blinded by this spell. Undead and oozes have disadvantage on this saving throw.</p> <p><strong><em>Versatile.</em></strong> This weapon can be used with one or two hands. A damage value in parentheses appears with the property&mdash;the damage when the weapon is used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":0,"units":""},"target":{"value":0,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":5,"long":0,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"str","actionType":"mwak","attackBonus":1,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d8+1+@mod","slashing"]],"versatile":"1d10+1+@mod"},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":0,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":10},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"weaponType":"martialM","properties":{"ver":true,"amm":false,"fin":false,"fir":false,"foc":false,"hvy":false,"lgt":false,"lod":false,"rch":false,"rel":false,"ret":false,"spc":false,"thr":false,"two":false},"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.9j0hgdLSxkSftWBX"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Ceremonial_Macuahuitl.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"uige6wMa5QilH3bg","name":"Magehunter Blade (Legendary)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, legendary (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Made of a weave-intersecting alloy, these armaments were the go-to weapon for the mage-hunting Order of the Spellbreakers. Fanatical elements within the order have recently taken power, bringing with them an abhorrence for all things magical. Having largely destroyed this magical cache, such weapons are now very rare and are only wielded by the few who cling to the old ways.</p>\n<p>You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you hit a target that is under the effect of a spell or magical effect, the spell is dispelled if it is 7th-level or lower, and the target takes an additional [[/r 1d8]] force damage for each level of the dispelled spell (dispelled cantrips deal no additional damage). Once a spell is dispelled, roll a [[/r d8]]. If the number is equal to or lower than the level of the dispelled spell, the blade loses this feature until the following dawn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.xMkP8BmFzElcsMaR]{Greatsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.aS3OAt3G9Ru2lApa]{Magehunter Greatsword (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.10ZP2Bu3vnCuYMIB]{Longsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.v3yN3vlJNhKF5oeU]{Magehunter Longsword (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.Tobce1hexTnDk4sV]{Rapier} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.dMKkC6U0uofH9UVz]{Magehunter Rapier (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.fbC0Mg1a73wdFbqO]{Scimitar} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.vY4QlXa0gXEPvuyD]{Magehunter Scimitar (Legendary)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.osLzOwQdPtrK3rQH]{Shortsword} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.dIw8Sv5PupQVGsmf]{Magehunter Shortsword (Legendary)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Legendary","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.bs8hlL6wDs8mS0Zz"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Magehunter_Blade.webp","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vke886lxlmSO1cpk","name":"Plate of Magehunter General (Uncommon)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"loot","data":{"description":{"value":"<p><em>Generic variant, uncommon (requires attunement)</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Made of a dark grey, lead-rich metal, this plate seems especially dull around magical sources of light.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Absorption.</em></strong> When you are subjected to a magical effect that allows you to make a saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage on a success and only half as much damage on a failure. The metal of the armor hums with the absorbed energy; once you have used this feature, you may not do so again until you finish a long rest, after which time the absorbed energy dissipates.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Base items.</em></strong> This item variant can be applied to the following base items:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.SK2HATQ4abKUlV8i]{Breastplate} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.kR6S97b28mvznJji]{Breastplate of Magehunter General (Uncommon)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.vsgmACFYINloIdPm]{Half Plate Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.pebiYZM9Wg1QCu1B]{Half Plate Armor of Magehunter General (Uncommon)})</li>\n<li>@Compendium[dnd5e.items.OjkIqlW2UpgFcjZa]{Plate Armor} (@Compendium[free-loot-tavern-compendium.free-loot-tavern-variant-compendium.IaitkDcmFfrUnAkB]{Plate Armor of Magehunter General (Uncommon)})</li>\n</ul>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":true,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"damage":{"parts":[]}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.OvJz5DTWzfDTwBU5"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Plate_of_the_Magehunter_General.webp","effects":[]}
{"name":"Phantom Limb","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, uncommon</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This nebulous, floating cluster of green-blue light replaces a hand, arm, foot, leg, or similar absent appendage when you attune to it. Despite its spectral appearance, the <em>phantom limb</em> is solid and can&rsquo;t phase through any material or creature. You can make it appear or disappear at will (no action required). When present, it functions as the limb its replacing.</p>\n<p>If you have multiple <em>phantom limb</em>s, they count as a single magic item with regard to the number of magic items to which you can attune.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can detach the limb. While your <em>phantom limb</em> is detached it acts as described by the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Utk1OQRwYkMkFRD3]{Mage Hand}spell. You can use an action to reattach your limb as long as it is within 30 feet of you.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Uncommon","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"bonus","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.xOtXsW2OXLiX43wz"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantom_Limb.webp","effects":[],"_id":"xH7tmApOnVncfn6k"}
{"name":"Phantom Limb (Rare)","permission":{"default":0,"wNmVznqLqvLski4t":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"description":{"value":"\n<em>Wondrous item, rare</em>\n\n\n<hr />\n\n<p>This nebulous, floating cluster of green-blue light replaces a hand, arm, foot, leg, or similar absent appendage when you attune to it. Despite its spectral appearance, the phantom limb is solid and can&rsquo;t phase through any material or creature. You can make it appear or disappear at will (no action required). When present, it functions as the limb its replacing.</p>\n<p>If you have multiple phantom limbs, they count as a single magic item with regard to the number of magic items to which you can attune.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can detach the limb. While your phantom limb is detached it acts as described by the @Compendium[dnd5e.spells.Utk1OQRwYkMkFRD3]{Mage Hand}spell. You can use an action to reattach your limb as long as it is within 30 feet of you.</p>\n<p>The reach of your unarmed strikes made with the phantom limb and attacks you make with weapons with the light property held by the phantom limb have their reach increased by 5 feet.</p>\n","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"Loot Tavern","quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":null,"attuned":false,"equipped":true,"rarity":"Rare","identified":true,"activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":0,"max":0,"per":null},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"armor":{"value":null,"type":"bonus","dex":null},"hp":{"value":0,"max":0,"dt":null,"conditions":""},"speed":{"value":null,"conditions":""},"strength":null,"stealth":false,"proficient":true},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.loot-tavern-compendium.loot-taverns-magic-item-vault.CzQBcbrBL30NOEHw"}},"img":"modules/free-loot-tavern-compendium/artwork/Phantom_Limb.webp","effects":[],"_id":"zbJW9q4icsOtRK0O"}
